<TITLE> DST not a problem for coming winter: minister </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 26 (bdnews24.com)  The current Daylight Saving Time will not create any trouble during winter, state minister for power has said. "The government decided earlier that the existing clock time will not undergo any change," state minister Enamul Haque said at the launch of a conference at Osmani Hall auditorium on Monday. "The existing time will not pose any trouble during winter. No question arises over advantages or disadvantages of Daylight Saving Time. Rather question arises over its adjustment back," he said. The prime minister's adviser for energy affairs, Toufique-e-Elahi Chowdhury said, "The government has no plan to switch over to the previous timing and school students should not have any problem in coping with DST." Bangladesh's began implementing DST at 11pm local time on June 19, 2009 in a bid to save power and alleviate the nation's energy shortfall. The government had announced at one point that Bangladesh Standard Time would be revived from Oct 1 taking winter into account, but then changed its mind and decided to continue with DST. b
